name: cyclobutane, methylene-
Reason: 1,3-dioxolane has a melting point of -106.0 degrees Celsius. The basic unit for comparison can be ethylene, which has a melting point of -169.0 degrees Celsius. The methylene-cyclobutane has a melting point that is lower than ethylene due to the lack of a rigid ring structure. The cyclobutane ring itself does not contribute to the melting point due to the lack of hydrogen bonding.
